content:
@Alan McKee I love this topic. People connect to the emotion of lyrics way more than the literal story. yes, the lyrics are important in that catchy memorable things are important. But more than that, lyrics are the way to express a feeling. 

great songwriting, like great poetry, allows people to connect their own lives to words that aren't about them.

I didn't grow up in the hood in atlanta but I love Young Thug because I hear his joy and his pain and his bravado in his songs and my heart connects. I've never worked on a farm but when I hear "I ain't gonna work on Maggie's farm no more" by Bob Dylan I feel that rebellion and connect it to my life. When the chainsmokers sing "baby hold me closer in the backseat of your rover that you can't afford and your roommate back in boulder and the mattress that you stole" I know that feeling because I've been 20 and in love and in a crazy time in life.
